		/// <param name="WaitTimeOut">
		/// <para>The time-out interval for the retrieval operation, in milliseconds. The function returns if the interval elapses, even if no worker threads are queued to the completion list. If the <i>WaitTimeOut</i> parameter is zero, the completion list is checked for available worker threads without waiting for worker threads to become available. If the <i>WaitTimeOut</i> parameter is INFINITE, the function's time-out interval never elapses. This is not recommended, however, because it causes the function to block until one or more worker threads become available.</para>
